May 18th, 1899:

There was a meeting today. Usually, this wouldn't be worth my time; anything I needed to know could have been sent to me in a letter. Unfortunately, an Inventor retrieved me from my quarters to inform me that the Patriarchy had requested my presence. If it had not been for the nature of this meeting, I would have cut the insolent bastard's fingers off. 

They found it.

I had my doubts- ever since the church allowed females to ascend to any rank higher than Inventors, we've become completely incompetent. It was within my range of reasoning that the stupid whores had merely found another dishwasher. Regardless, my curiosity piqued, and I'm always more than happy to take any opportunity I can to prove Bumaro's decision wrong. 

The meeting was about as interesting as one would expect it to be. The endless, redundant dronings of Patriarchs far past their prime enabled constructs and ideas that would never come to pass before dragging themselves to the topic of discussion. A civilian had identified a construct in London back in January, and a Legate-Faithful has now confirmed it as a holy artifact. They wanted me to confirm the nature of the object and return it to Mexico. 

When I inquired about the pace at which the Legate returned, I was met with claims that a new "normalcy" agency had infiltrated the ranks of the British crown and that all members of the church were to exercise caution when traveling. It's highly likely this was merely a scare tactic Bumaro fabricated to keep church members close together, deceitful but clever. 

I have been instructed to depart from Tampico tomorrow morning. Originally, I was to be accompanied by a Hispanic, Columbian or something like that, a disgusting notion which I quickly dispelled. Instead, I am accompanied by Militant-Faithful Caesar Brogly and Inventor-Faithful Irwin Fordham alongside a group of forty general members of the faith. 

I will seek to exit London sooner than I enter it, the less time I have to spend in that FLESH pit, the better. 

]]



