| contents=

May 30th, 1899:

London. A vile hellhole serving as the epicenter of an equally vile country. What was once a glimmering city has since been ruined and tainted by the sins of The FLESH and the abolishment of slavery. I had previously considered the possibility of the stomach entering the city, but due to how fast items travel through London's ports, I figured it would be gone sooner than I would be able to investigate. 

We arrived in London through the St Katharine Docks, a dreadful place run by creatures that made me glad I didn't possess the senses of The FLESH. Unfortunately, our destination lay in the Southwark neighborhood, about two miles from the port. 

Same as four days ago, Brogly's presence has been a hindrance to our proceedings; he's a loggerhead and duller than a rock. His only redeeming quality is his 20/20 vision. The man's head has been clouded by a FLESH-bound lust for Saint Trunnion and her unholy teachings. He stated my mechanical form was bound to draw unsavory attention and wrestled me into a heinous disguise. If he fears a mechanical form so much, then I shall ensure he grows to love it...

A crumbling warehouse in a sea of other crumbling warehouses. I had heard a lot about the status of the man who discovered the stomach, so needless to say, this was not what I was expecting. Although much to my delight, Fordham had discovered a coffeehouse in the area, rumors stated that the coffee was harvested the way I like. 

The interior of the warehouse was disheveled and unsanitary, various catwalks lead to adjacent rooms, in the center of the warehouse floor sat a large object covered with a white sheet. 

Fordham introduced me to James Moriarty, a tall, thin man with skin lighter than the parchment I write this on. It was clear to me that this was a man possessed by desires of The FLESH. After our dreadful exchange of pleasantries, the man limped to the center of the room and pulled the sheet off the object.

It was just as beautiful as I imagined. A divine combination of gears and steel coming together in a form so striking words fail to truly give it meaning. 

"We acquired this warehouse following a recent operation." The man explained, "Once I grew closer to the object, I instantly knew of its importance and managed to contact one of your representatives." 

I wheeled over to the stomach, laying my hand upon its hard exterior. 

"You have done a great service to the church, but your services are no longer required," I said, focusing on our reflection in the cold steel. 

In my mind, I counted down from fifteen. At three, I heard the expected clang on the back of my head, followed by the usual reactionary movements from Brogly and his goons. 

"Tsk, off by three," I exclaimed as I turned to the pale man, his sunken eyes widened. I wheeled myself closer, feeling the vibrations of his FLESH and bone. 

"Professor Moriarty, do you take me for an idiot?" I inquired, met only with the sound of the frail man's heartbeat. 

With a flick of his wrist, the man produced a scimitar knife engraved with spurious gold. He brought the knife down upon my head, lodging its blade in my skull. I retaliated by detaining Moriarty's hands; the eternally satisfying sound of bones cracking graced my ears as I peeled his fingers back.

Through his other sleeve, the man produced a syringe, a tactic just as effective as the knife. 

"Well, isn't that just adorable?" My hand enclosed itself around his long neck, I sensed the vibrations of his pulse, faster and faster and faster.

"It's a real shame; you would've been a valuable asset." My fingers dug themselves through his neck, spilling the sinful liquids on the floor. 

The sack of FLESH dropped to the ground as I extended a lone finger to the catwalks above, demanding that Brogly bring me the gunman. Despite Brogly's asininity, he was well trained, and the gunman was brought to me within moments. 

He was quite different from the nearby corpse. Large, hairy, primitive, he would do nicely. I directed Brogly and the gunman up the stairs and onto the catwalks above the stomach's opening. Brogly's vacant eyes stared at me, seeking the reassurance he was shortly met with. With a push, the man tumbled from the catwalks, crashing into the cavity below. 

I was met with the orgasmic sound of churning gears and screaming FLESH. The other end of the construct dispensed several gears, bullets, and a large container holding a specimen I was quite familiar with. A gracious gift from MEKHANE. 

I listened to the utterances muttered beneath the breaths of the church members. 

"Caesar, your right hand."

He was apprehensive; I wheeled myself closer, neglecting to reiterate myself. 

A swift cut of my blade and three of the fingers on Brogly's right hand were lost to the stomach's opening. The momentary squealing of FLESH and another gift, three mechanical rodents glimmering and golden. 

"Let something like that happen again, and your entire body will meet the same fate." 

"Moriarty's corpse is to be hung from the rafters," I called to the group down below. "His FLESH will be of great use to me."






<br>
<br>

June 2nd, 1899:

The rats are gone. 

They got out of the warehouse a couple of days ago, stuck around the alleyways for a while, but now they're completely gone. 

I worry not about this being a problem; they'll likely be deducted as mere children's toys. 

]]

