**Volume 02.07.30-36**
**30.** To fabricate the gut was a daunting task. 
**31.** Orville would spend hundreds of moons studying MEKHANE's form.##red|^^a^^##
**32.** Jacob would provide the metals necessary to construct the stomach while, much to Jacob's dismay, Orville would isolate himself from the rest of Amoni for several seasons at a time to complete his project.
**33.** With the encroaching war and rising tensions throughout the patriarchy,##red|^^b^^##
 Jacob feared his brother would be unable to complete the stomach. As such, he pressed Orville into the completion of the canal. 
**34.** Within a fortnight, the brothers were certain the construct was complete. Orville, confident in his technology, would sacrifice his rightmost toe to the stomach; to his dismay, the construct would activate, but no FLESH would be converted or destroyed. 
**35.** Jacob, now called to fight the [https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/rounderhouse-jade-proposal Covenant], ##red|^^c^^## urged his brother to seek ancient texts and inscriptions for the location of the missing component.
**36.** And so a new journey would begin for the sons of Kadmiel. 

