##red|a.##  At this point in the war, ranking members injured in battle returned to Amoni as the development of all prosthetics had shifted to the city.

##red|b.## Amoni was built atop a labyrinth structure of steel. Only the highest-ranking members of the church were allowed to descend into the labyrinth due to its precarious nature. See Volume 12.88.444 for more. 

##red|c.## Due to the current condition of Amoni, excavation of the subterranean portion of the city is currently impossible, further details of Orville and Jacob's descent into the city have been considered lost. 
[[/div]]

**Volume 02.07.227-235**
**227.** And so Jacob and Orville, the sons of Kadmiel, would be reunited once again. Jacob returned to Amoni following his battlefield injuries. ##red|^^a^^## While Orville had rejoined the city following his investigation of the [https://wanderers-library.wikidot.com ancient libraries].
**228.** Upon reconnecting with his brother, Orville would unveil the [# ancient text] he had discovered. 
**229.** "It spoke to me!" Orville would exclaim. "It lured me to its location, screaming for me to rip it off the shelf." 
**230.** "I seized the text from its hiding spot and opened its contents. Instead of being met with text and numbers, I peered into the eyes of MEKHANE and saw all that exists." 
**231.** "She instructed me to descend to the deeper layers of Amoni, ##red|^^b^^## there I would find the component which I seek." 
**232.** "I implore you, Jacob, to accompany me to the labyrinth, and together we shall finally complete this quest!"
**233.** Jacob would ponder this call before finally accepting the offer. Together, the two brothers would descend into the labyrinth. 
**234.** Various trials ##red|^^c^^## would lead the brothers to a previously undiscovered chamber.
**235.** The room would host a component; constructed of the purest fuladh, composed of a form so divine the languages of the FLESH fail to describe its brilliance. 
