I will personally tear the skin off of John Watson's back. 

June 8th, 1899: 

For once, one of the bumbling idiots managed to accomplish something. Holmes was infected just as planned, but that has not deterred his accomplice. How that moronic bastard is a doctor is far beyond my understanding. 

Holmes was getting close, I'll admit that much, but how Watson works is far beyond me. He's getting closer. Saw right through the disguise of one of our agents; must've heard the ticking. We haven't seen the man since. Brogly wanted to pull our agents back to the warehouse, but I refused. He claims to have lost four agents, but it's clear he's spewing hot air. They've all been arrested and dragged to Scotland Yard. It doesn't matter; they'd have to dissect our agents to learn the truth, and the Brits just don't have the heart to do it. 

Fordham brought upon me the Schema I wrote, reminding me that the further an individual is intertwined with their FLESH, the greater the sacrifice. I have demanded the general delegation bring me more humans, preferably ones who wouldn't be missed, but that appears to not be enough. The stomach keeps spitting out the same components, and if I wish to transform the corpse into something truly divine, this won't cut it. 

Regardless, Fordham's still been quite useful. He's taken in my footsteps, extracting the entrails from the corpses we receive and replacing the innards with clockwork mechanisms. It's clear my intellect is unmatched, an underground network to transport the stomach out of the city, a cogitation even Bumaro would fail to think up! 

The construct is coming along well. We abducted several lawyers and, in return, received computational devices; when attached, we managed to simulate a brain in the construct. Moriarty's corpse is now eternally unyielding to me. He stands at six and a half feet tall, electing to equip the corpse with four legs for movement and eight arms to extract different parts from a human corpse. All that remains is to gift my beautiful creation with sight. 

June 9th, 1899:

Brogly is gone. 

He approached me this morning claiming that Watson wasn't the only one hot on our tail, that the coffee runs and abductions were warranting unwanted attention. Of course, the idiot can only see what's directly in front of him, failing to realize why we needed to distribute our members across the city. 

He stormed off, claiming that he was going to deal with Watson himself. For once, I thought he was finally going to be useful- naturally, I was mistaken. He came crawling back in the dead of night, whining that he was intercepted by members of British intelligence. It was made clear to me that he had failed in his mission and ended up leaking our operations to an extremely incompetent government run by a WOMAN!

I gouged Brogly's eyes out with my own hands, forcing him to listen to his eyes be churned and processed in the stomach before throwing him in as well. Through the destruction of his FLESH, Caesar Brogly managed to contribute something noteworthy to our cause. Through the components MEKHANE has graced us with, I have managed to construct a new image processing system capable of allowing me to connect with the occipital implants Fordham inserts into our agents. Soon, I shall have eyes all across London, allowing me to handpick our next recipients of MEKHANES grace. I will construct perfection, no matter the cost. 

June 10th, 1899:

They're everywhere, they're in our ranks, outside our warehouse, in the deepest corners of my mind. In my slumber, I was met with visions of Amoni and subsequent visions of my own demise. A traitor exists in our midst, waiting to strike me, and I will find them. 

June 11th, 1899: 

Twelve sacrifices today, four of them our own. I'm not taking risks, not when I'm this close. I tested the new image processing device today, and I have now seen the repugnant face of Dr. John Watson. He approached one of my agents stationed in a nearby restaurant. 

His pug-like lips flapped, spewing unnecessary nonsense. My agent showed Watson to his table, careful to keep an eye on the obese doctor. Another man approached, an officer, lanky, his facial hair akin to that of a filthy rodent. I managed to catch his name, one born of FLESH rite: Lestrade. 

Despite the situation that surrounded him, Watson was cheery, approaching Lestrade with a kind manner and presenting an understanding tone when the officer failed to provide any leads on Holmes' condition. Every sentence exchanged between the two disgusted me more- two incompetent and ignorant morons encouraging each other's oafishness. 

Following their meeting, Lestrade was brought to me and sacrificed, yielding nothing more than a few simple gears. 

John Watson is not a threat. He will spend the rest of eternity stumbling in the dark as his accomplice turns to steel. I thought no man could be that slow, no matter the false god they worship; I stand corrected. 

I will have the members of the general faith deal with Watson while I complete the construction of Moriarty's corpse & ostracize our traitor. 

