June 12th, 1899: 

Twenty sacrifices today. All of them blasphemous in their own right. I will purge every last member to find this rat if it means the last of me. 

The Moriarty construct is nearly complete, a perfect symbol of divine grace assembled to perform every service the church ever needs. I have granted it the ability to roam the warehouse with explicit permission to decommission anyone who comes in its path. Unfortunately, it has not proven itself yet. That vile rat is still amongst us; I know it to be true. 

Watson still encroaches closer every day, every step he takes is another towards me. I see it now, this man has set out to kill me and will not rest. He has sent me fake letters from the Patriarchy in Mexico requesting my return. He's trying to pull me out of my hiding place. A broken clock is right twice a day, and with the assistance of a filthy rat, that number can jump drastically. 

I watch him through a hundred different eyes, and I wish to kill him. He claims to be a man of science yet denies the foundational science that composes our church. 

<i> I want to tear every bone from his body, denying him any sense of structure. </i>

He follows a baseless reasoning of "deduction," desperately seeking to tie together seemingly random details in a futile attempt to push his own agenda. 

<br>

<i> I want to purge his eyes from their sockets and bathe in the blood that follows. </i>

He claims to be a friend of these people, yet he takes from them, offering nothing in return. 

<i> I want to shatter his brain into puny sizes of meat and feed them to the stomach. </i>

He follows his insufferable hero, Sherlock Holmes, like a starving puppy. His undying affection for a man who merely does nothing more than perform simple parlor tricks. John Watson has no personality outside of his false hero. 

<i> I want to shred his skin, relieve him of FLESH.</i>

I want to save him. I must save him. I know it; he just needs a little push. 






June 13th, 1899: 

I see it now. It's Fordham; it's always been Fordham. 

"We can't use that component; the construct will become unstable."

"We should ignore this Watson fellow and focus on getting the stomach back to Mexico."

"I'm afraid I can't give you that component and still be sound of mind."

All lies, all of it. 

He manipulated Brogly; he dissented from my followers, he lied to our superiors in Mexico. He wants the stomach for himself. He wants to achieve perfection, but perfection does not exist for those who bring hell upon their brethren. 

My coffee runner did not return today. I personally went to investigate to find the store closed down and my runner nowhere in sight; it was a front to watch me. When I returned, I could see the glimmer in Fordham's eyes; it was him, it's always been him.

He is a master of FLESH, clever and cunning. His screams echoed through the warehouse as his body churned through the stomach, a ringing reminder of sacrilege that will always stain these walls. 

I care not for what becomes of the stomach; it is of no use to me anymore. My construct is complete. My time is limited; the walls are closing in. I only have one goal now.

<i> I must save Doctor John Watson. I must grant him the gift of eternal life.</i>

