They're almost all gone. I gifted them to MEKHANE, and she gifted them eternal life. If I cannot save Watson, I can save my people. Holmes will be perfected soon, and Watson will realize what he missed. 

I care not to return to Mexico. Those bumbling idiots have no concept of what the stomach is capable of; it will rot and collect dust as it creeps towards a reconstruction that will never come to pass. 

The walls are closing in; the crown has detained my automatons; Watson knows my plan, and all will come to pass. I intend to hold my final ground here in a brilliant display of my greatest invention. My construct will fight for me; he will tear through the sinful bastards while I give eternal life to the remaining members of the church. 

Orville was wrong, he always was. There is no purpose more divine than to surrender your FLESH to the stomach of MEKHANE. I was the first to do so, and I have achieved perfection ever since. 

The stomach blessed me with the privilege of eternal life, forcing me to witness the collapse of Amoni with my own eyes. At that moment, I should have understood the futility of the church. 

I revoke my brother, the patriarchy, all of it, for now, I understand true apotheosis. 

